    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "When you talk about the risk of \"losing their foundational identity,\" it sounds like you're suggesting that the influx of these groups is almost inherently destabilizing. Some people see this as a form of soft replacement where the original culture is eventually overwhelmed. From an analytical standpoint, is there a point where the sheer scale of demographic change makes it impossible for the original Western frameworks to survive, or are you saying the \"clashing\" values will inevitably lead to a breakdown of the current system?",
